$ Vim modes

The seven *basic* and seven *addtional* modes.

{ Basic modes

  table { ll
    → development/vim/editing/modes/normal ☰ 
    → development/vim/editing/modes/visual ☰
    select mode ☰
    → development/vim/editing/modes/insert ☰ 
    → development/vim/editing/modes/command-line ☰ aka Cmdline mode, used to enter → development/vim/commands[ex commands], pattern search commands (`/`, `?`) and the filter command (`!`)
    Ex mode ☰
    Terminal-Job mode ☰
  table }

}
{ Additional modes

  table { ll

    Operator-pending mode ☰
    Replace mode ☰
    Virtual replace mode ☰
    Insert normal mode ☰
    Terminal-normal mode ☰
    Insert Visual mode ☰
    Insert Select mode ☰

  table }

}
